Readme

This script was designed for setting up on a raspberry pi as a red team implant to start compromising before you remote into it. But it can also be a handy way of kicking off the first stage of an internal network pentest whilst you start other tasks.

For the PI build

This script can be run on boot by adding it to your system's startup scripts. On a Debian-based system, you can do this by adding it to the /etc/rc.local file. Make sure to make the script executable with the chmod +x command before adding it to the startup scripts.
